snippet.textDisplay: I am going through the exact same thing as you and I wish I could just fly to New Jersey and give you guys a big hug but I live all the way in Australia. Last year January 19th I lost my mum to cancer. First she had breast cancer, brain cancer and then it moved into her back and into her blood (leukaemia). It was a really tough time for me and felt hopeless. I never wanted to cry because it made me feel weak and I also avoided looking at old photos and stuff so I wouldn't. I never thought this type of thing would happen to our family. When my mum sat us all down at the table and said she only had 1 year to live I had a wave of anxiety rush over me. I had been living in complete fear for 3 years and that really hit me like a bus. 5 days later the time halved and every day it just got shorter and shorter to the point that it got from 1 year to 3 days over the span of a month. One day I came home from gymnastics and all my Italian relatives were there and them and my dad sat me and my brother down at the table. I will never forget my brother saying "No don't tell me it happened" and my dad whispering under his breath "yes". That was the most tragic day of my life. Just thought I would share my story with you guys because I feel like we went through very similar things. I will be donating $250 to your foundation to support cancer foundations to stop this stupid disease. Ethans haircut looks great by the way. ily❤️❤️
